First you create the application window. Then you add components to the window. Then you write code that is executed when the user performs a certain action, for example when she enters text into a [JTextComponent](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/text.html) or when she clicks on a [JButton](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/button.html). The code that gets executed in response to a user action is referred to as an [event listener](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/events/index.html).

